    "text": "There's an early hint, but it isn't solid yet. In 7 tagged evening-lift days versus 33 comparison days, you slept roughly 24 minutes less on average — but with only 7 tagged days that's a low-confidence pattern, and it could just as easily be the things that travel with evening sessions: later dinner, later shower, screens while winding down. Last night fits loosely — after yesterday's 51-minute strength session you slept 415 minutes, about 23 minutes under your 7-day average of 438 minutes, though your HRV is 62 ms, close to your 30-day average of 62.5 ms, so nothing systemic is showing. What would settle it: keep tagging evening lifts for a few more weeks, and note dinner time on those days. If the gap survives 15 or so tagged days, treat it as actionable and try shifting key sessions earlier; if it shrinks, the routine around the lifting was probably the signal.",
